BT /F1 10 Tf 0.080 0.100 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 28.00 485.00 Tm 13 TL
(The project raises several ethical issues connected to privacy, fairness, user trust, and responsible) Tj
T*
(handling of data. A system that stores tenant identities, contact details, lease information, and) Tj
T*
(payment history must be designed in a way that respects individuals and avoids unnecessary exposure of) Tj
T*
(private information.) Tj
ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 0.080 0.100 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 38.00 425.00 Tm 13 TL
(- Tenant information should only be visible to authorised users with a legitimate operational) Tj
ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 0.080 0.100 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 50.00 412.00 Tm 13 TL
(reason to access it.) Tj
ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 0.080 0.100 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 38.00 391.00 Tm 13 TL
(- The system should not permit one tenant to view another tenant's private financial or complaint) Tj
ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 0.080 0.100 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 50.00 378.00 Tm 13 TL
(data.) Tj
ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 0.080 0.100 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 38.00 357.00 Tm 13 TL
(- Role design should promote fair and proportionate access rather than granting excessive) Tj
ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 0.080 0.100 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 50.00 344.00 Tm 13 TL
(privileges by default.) Tj
ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 0.080 0.100 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 38.00 323.00 Tm 13 TL
(- Simulated payment features must be clearly understood as academic demonstrations rather than) Tj
ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 0.080 0.100 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 50.00 310.00 Tm 13 TL
(real financial processing.) Tj
ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 0.080 0.100 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 28.00 289.00 Tm 13 TL
(An ethical system should also support transparency. Users should understand what kind of information is) Tj
T*
(stored, who can access it, and why certain permissions exist. Even in a coursework prototype, the design) Tj
T*
(should reflect responsible thinking about trust and digital accountability.) Tj
ET
