BT /F1 10 Tf 0.080 0.100 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 28.00 357.00 Tm 13 TL
(Sustainability in software includes technical sustainability, maintainability, and the efficient use of) Tj
T*
(resources over time. In this project, sustainability is reflected more in the structure and longevity of) Tj
T*
(the system than in raw environmental impact alone.) Tj
ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 0.080 0.100 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 38.00 310.00 Tm 13 TL
(- The modular codebase supports long-term maintainability because the interface, services,) Tj
ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 0.080 0.100 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 50.00 297.00 Tm 13 TL
(validation, business rules, and data access logic are separated.) Tj
ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 0.080 0.100 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 38.00 276.00 Tm 13 TL
(- Persistent relational storage reduces duplication and supports more consistent long-term data) Tj
ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 0.080 0.100 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 50.00 263.00 Tm 13 TL
(management.) Tj
ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 0.080 0.100 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 38.00 242.00 Tm 13 TL
(- A reusable seed dataset improves testing, demonstration, and future development without repeated) Tj
ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 0.080 0.100 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 50.00 229.00 Tm 13 TL
(manual setup.) Tj
ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 0.080 0.100 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 38.00 208.00 Tm 13 TL
(- A desktop solution has lower deployment complexity for coursework, though a future web version) Tj
ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 0.080 0.100 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 50.00 195.00 Tm 13 TL
(could improve scalability and access efficiency.) Tj
ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 0.080 0.100 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 28.00 174.00 Tm 13 TL
(From an environmental perspective, the application is relatively lightweight and runs on standard) Tj
T*
(hardware without unusual computational demand. However, the more important sustainability contribution) Tj
